<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1954,2019]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,152,448]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="2" pageNumber="50">
Only one female specimen (
<figureCitation box="[485,586,1954,1980]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="2.[151,273,1746,1770]" captionTargetBox="[204,1392,187,1723]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[183,1411,179,1723]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Types of skipper taxa described by Jinhaku Sonan: 1 – 3, holotype of Lobocla kodairai, upperside, underside, labels; 4 – 6, holotype of Coladenia sadakoe, upperside, underside, labels; 7 – 9, holotype of Tagiades menaka kotoshona, upperside, underside, labels; 10 – 12, holotype of Notocrypta arisana, upperside, underside, labels; 13 – 15, holotype of Ampittia maro matsumurai, upperside, underside, labels; 16 – 18. holotype of Augiades bouddha niitakana, upperside, underside, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189655/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[541,586,1954,1980]" pageId="2" pageNumber="50" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
) was included in Sonan’s (
<number box="[908,970,1954,1980]" pageId="2" pageNumber="50" value="1936.0">1936</number>
) original description of this taxon. The material bearing the 
<typeStatus box="[399,450,1993,2019]" pageId="2" pageNumber="50">type</typeStatus>
label (
<figureCitation box="[534,605,1993,2019]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="2.[151,273,1746,1770]" captionTargetBox="[204,1392,187,1723]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[183,1411,179,1723]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Types of skipper taxa described by Jinhaku Sonan: 1 – 3, holotype of Lobocla kodairai, upperside, underside, labels; 4 – 6, holotype of Coladenia sadakoe, upperside, underside, labels; 7 – 9, holotype of Tagiades menaka kotoshona, upperside, underside, labels; 10 – 12, holotype of Notocrypta arisana, upperside, underside, labels; 13 – 15, holotype of Ampittia maro matsumurai, upperside, underside, labels; 16 – 18. holotype of Augiades bouddha niitakana, upperside, underside, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189655/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[590,605,1993,2019]" pageId="2" pageNumber="50" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) matches the original description. 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1023,1183,1993,2019]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" refString="Evans, W. H. (1949) A catalogue of the Hesperiidae from Europe, Asia and Australia in the British Museum (Natural History). The British Museum (Natural History), London, xix + 502 pp." type="book" year="1949">
Evans (
<number box="[1112,1174,1993,2019]" pageId="2" pageNumber="50" value="1949.0">1949</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName box="[1281,1382,1993,2018]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lobocla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kodairai">
<emphasis box="[1281,1382,1993,2018]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="50">kodairai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bremer &amp; Grey, 1853" authorityName="Bremer &amp; Grey" authorityYear="1853" box="[307,846,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lobocla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis box="[307,542,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">Lobocla bifasciata</emphasis>
(Bremer &amp; Grey, 
<number box="[771,837,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1853.0">1853</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Shirozu" box="[938,1119,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refString="Shirozu, T. (1944) Notes on some Formosan butterflies (I). (Records of three species new to the fauna of Formosa). Transactions of Kansai Entomological Society, 14, 30 - 42. [In Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1944">
Shirôzu (
<number box="[1053,1119,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1944.196">1944</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shirozu" box="[1133,1197,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refString="Shirozu, T. (1960) Butterflies of Formosa in Colour. Hoikusha, Osaka, 481 pp. [In Japanese]" type="book" year="1960">1960</bibRefCitation>
) retained the name 
<taxonomicName box="[151,252,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lobocla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kodairai">
<emphasis box="[151,252,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">kodairai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecific name. 
<taxonomicName box="[536,758,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lobocla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis box="[536,758,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">Lobocla bifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows tremendous variation especially in male genitalia (
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[159,302,229,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refString="Evans, W. H. (1949) A catalogue of the Hesperiidae from Europe, Asia and Australia in the British Museum (Natural History). The British Museum (Natural History), London, xix + 502 pp." type="book" year="1949">
Evans 
<number box="[239,302,229,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1949.0">1949</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). There is no doubt that this taxon belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[838,953,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lobocla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis box="[838,953,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">bifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or its complex because its male genitalia (
<bibRefCitation author="Shirozu" box="[159,319,268,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refString="Shirozu, T. (1960) Butterflies of Formosa in Colour. Hoikusha, Osaka, 481 pp. [In Japanese]" type="book" year="1960">
Shirôzu 
<number box="[259,319,268,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1960.0">1960</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) agree with those of 
<taxonomicName box="[566,681,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lobocla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis box="[566,681,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">bifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in order to judge whether the Taiwanese taxon is distinct or not, further investigation is required. 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[601,763,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refString="Evans, W. H. (1949) A catalogue of the Hesperiidae from Europe, Asia and Australia in the British Museum (Natural History). The British Museum (Natural History), London, xix + 502 pp." type="book" year="1949">
Evans (
<number box="[691,753,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1949.0">1949</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
suspected that 
<taxonomicName box="[948,1049,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lobocla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kodairai">
<emphasis box="[948,1049,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">kodairai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be represented by a stray specimen, evidently an erroneous view as this taxon has been shown to be a montane skipper native to the island (
<bibRefCitation author="Shirozu" box="[239,405,384,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refString="Shirozu, T. (1960) Butterflies of Formosa in Colour. Hoikusha, Osaka, 481 pp. [In Japanese]" type="book" year="1960">
Shirôzu 
<number box="[342,405,384,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1960.0">1960</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yamanaka" box="[419,617,384,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refString="Yamanaka, M. (1980) Distribution of Formosan butterflies. Tyo to Ga 30, suppl. 1, 1 - 143. [In Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1980">
Yamanaka 
<number box="[552,617,384,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). We tentatively follow Shirôzu’s (
<number box="[1037,1175,384,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1944.196">1944, 1960</number>
) treatment, regarding 
<taxonomicName authority="Sonan, 1936" authorityName="Sonan" authorityYear="1936" box="[151,404,422,448]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lobocla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kodairai">
<emphasis box="[151,250,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">kodairai</emphasis>
Sonan, 
<number box="[345,404,422,448]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1936.0">1936</number>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecific name of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bremer &amp; Grey, 1853" authorityName="Bremer &amp; Grey" authorityYear="1853" box="[705,1210,422,448]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lobocla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis box="[705,923,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">Lobocla bifasciata</emphasis>
(Bremer &amp; Grey, 
<number box="[1138,1201,422,448]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" value="1853.0">1853</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
